Creating cucumber framework from scratch:
First go to Intellij
Then create a project with Gradle(Select any other build tool if required)
Set Java version if present
Click on Apply
Add the plugins by going to settings
Add the dependecies in build.gradle in Cucumber, Junit, Selenium, Junit jupiter for assertions from maven website - https://mvnrepository.com/
cucumber = Cucumber JVM: Java
Junit - Junit platform or Junit 5, JUnit Jupiter (Aggregator)
Selenium - Selenium Java
Webdriver Manager - WebDriverManager(Not github icon one)

Create a feature file in resources - by adding .feature in the file, the feature file will be created. The feature file shjould be green in color after creation
Now start POJO, create a package at java directory of "com.cucumberscript"
Inside that create a TestRunner class
Create packages for different purposes Pages, step definitions, utilities
Give all the annotations and don't add any methods in the class as annotations will take care
Create LoginStepdefs class
Now mouse hoverover, click on more actions or create step definition for all. After give  path "LoginStepdefs"
Methods should have created
create "GetBrowserDriver" for the drivers details and to call them
Now to create the implemented methods, create the base classes
Write the initialization methods and closing methods
Create Hooks in setdefs package and call those base methods. Apply annotations.
In the base class, write the methods for Initialzation of driver and closing methods
Create config folder and add required properties files as application.properties, framework.properties etc.,
Enter the details to avoid hardcoding like URL, Username, pswds
Create a "login page" class and add webelements, methods
call parameter values from properties and use page factor here
Call those methods and in the step defs class
Now execute the script from Test runner









